---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import SiteHeader from '../components/SiteHeader.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Greybrainer Lens | Manifesto"
  description="The editorial thesis behind Greybrainer Lens: a serious movie intelligence publication built for the streaming era."
>
  <SiteHeader />
  <section class="shell archive-hero">
    <span class="section-kicker">Manifesto</span>
    <h1>A movie intelligence publication, not a content farm.</h1>
    <p>
      Lens is meant to sit closer to a cultural magazine than a generic review blog. It should publish with the confidence of a critic,
      the curiosity of a researcher, and the editorial discipline of a serious newsroom.
    </p>
  </section>
  <section class="shell manifesto-longform">
    <div>
      <h2>What we publish</h2>
      <p>Daily briefings, deep research, screen politics, audience studies, OTT behaviour, and film criticism that names the social pattern underneath the plot.</p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h2>What we avoid</h2>
      <p>Thin SEO sludge, generic celebrity chatter, and interchangeable entertainment copy that could belong to any site on the internet.</p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <h2>Why Astro</h2>
      <p>Because the public site should be fast, crawlable, elegant, and structurally editorial from day one, while Greybrainer remains the internal creation engine behind it.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <Footer />
</BaseLayout>
